CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 6, 1958, pg. 23, reads: "It's All Over - Pittsburgh Steeler fullback Paul (Tank) Younger and defensive half-back Dean Darby are obviously down in the dumps following the team;s 17-10 loss to the Chicago Bears at Pitt Stadium last Saturday.  For the third game in a row, the Steelers failed to display any type of offense. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Steelers football players no. 35 Paul "Tank" Younger and no. 27 Dean Darby, in passageway of Pitt Stadium after game with Chicago Bears
